Miraa farmers might soon have a reason to smile should their proposals be adopted by the agriculture committee. The farmers while presenting their grievances before the agriculture committee in its tour of the miraa growing zones, farmers want the government to expedite the process of securing foreign markets, standardization of prices, and its destigmatization. The committee vice-chair Catherine Waruguru expressed interest in rooting for the establishment says of a miraa board. KTN's Allan Ochanda unpacks what this means for miraa farmers.
